article.headline: Morehead St. 49, Davidson 21
article.story: DAVIDSON, N.C. (AP) -- Nick Feldman caught one touchdown pass and returned a punt for another score as Morehead State held off a Davidson rally for a 49-21 victory in the Pioneer Football League Saturday. The Wildcats whittled away at a 24-7 deficit in the second quarter and cut the gap to 27-21 on Ryan Alexander's 7-yard scoring pass to Kirk Konert with 8:37 left in the third quarter. Davidson had the football late in the third period, but Alexander threw the second of his three interceptions, and the Eagles (4-1, 2-0 PFL) converted it into Brian Yost's 19-yard scoring pass to Erick Fitzpatrick with 13:17 left to play. Feldman took Cody Elder's punt and rambled 55 yards to boost Morehead State's lead to 42-21 with 6:35 left. Davidson (3-2, 1-1 PFL) failed to convert a fourth-and-4 at the Morehead State 43, and the Eagles went 57 yards for their final score on Kyle Redden's 25-yard run with 2:43 left. Feldman caught nine passes for 141 yards for the Eagles, including a 72-yard touchdown pass from Yost on the team's first offensive play. Alexander also threw three touchdown passes, including a 67-yard play to Myles Potter on the third play of the game.
